## Customizing Dashboards

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Goldenhunter1206/sellfaster_content/main/public/site/images/user-guide/team-account/dashboards/image.png)

### Layout Editing

Dashboards use a grid-based layout:

- Drag & drop widgets to reposition
- Resize widgets by dragging corners
- Layout changes auto-save

### Widget Options

For each widget you can:

- **Edit** - Modify configuration
- **Delete** - Remove from dashboard

### Auto-Refresh

Widget data automatically refreshes every 60 seconds to keep information current.

## Dashboard Settings

### Accessing Settings

1. Open your dashboard
1. Click the **Settings** button in the toolbar
1. Or click **Settings** from the dashboard list

### Available Settings

{% table %}
- Setting
- Description
---
- **Name**
- Dashboard title
---
- **Description**
- Purpose of the dashboard
---
- **Privacy**
- Private or shared
{% /table %}

### Deleting a Dashboard

1. Go to dashboard settings
1. Click **Delete Dashboard**
1. Confirm deletion

> **Warning:** Deleting a dashboard removes all its widgets and cannot be undone.

## Dashboard Permissions

### Permission Levels

{% table %}
- Level
- Capabilities
---
- **View**
- See widget data (read-only)
---
- **Edit**
- Add, modify, and delete widgets
{% /table %}

### Managing Permissions

Dashboard creators can manage who has access:

1. Open dashboard settings
1. Navigate to permissions section
1. Add users or roles with specific permission levels
1. Remove access as needed

### Assigning Permissions

Permissions can be assigned to:

- **Specific users** - Grant access to individual team members
- **Roles** - Grant access to everyone with a specific role (e.g., all managers)

## Default Dashboard

### Setting a Default

Set a dashboard as your default landing page:

1. From the dashboard list, click the menu on a dashboard
1. Select **Set as Default**
1. This dashboard opens when you visit the dashboards page

### Your Default is Yours

Each user can have their own default dashboard. This setting is personal and doesn't affect other team members.

## Audit History

Team owners can view the change history for dashboards:

1. Click the menu on a dashboard
1. Select **View Audit History**
1. See who made changes and when

This includes changes to dashboard settings and widgets.

## Best Practices

### Dashboard Design

1. **Keep it focused** - One purpose per dashboard
1. **Prioritize key metrics** - Most important at the top-left
1. **Use appropriate widgets** - Match visualization to data type
1. **Don't overcrowd** - Leave white space for readability

### Widget Selection

{% table %}
- Use Case
- Recommended Widget
---
- Single key number
- Metric Card
---
- Progress toward goal
- KPI Card
---
- Compare categories
- Bar Chart
---
- Trends over time
- Line Chart
---
- Show proportions
- Pie/Doughnut Chart
---
- Detailed records
- Data Table
{% /table %}

### Permission Management

1. **Start private** - Create dashboards privately first
1. **Share when ready** - Make shared after configuration is complete
1. **Use roles** - Assign permissions to roles for easier management
1. **Review periodically** - Audit who has access to sensitive dashboards

## Troubleshooting

### Widget Shows No Data

1. Verify filter settings aren't too restrictive
1. Check the time range configuration
1. Ensure data exists for the selected criteria
1. Try editing and re-saving the widget

### Permission Issues

If you can't view or edit a dashboard:

1. Verify you have the appropriate permission level
1. Contact the dashboard creator to request access
1. Check if you're in the correct team account

### Performance Issues

If dashboards are slow:

1. Reduce the number of widgets
1. Narrow time ranges
1. Use simpler aggregations

## Exporting as PDF

You can export any team dashboard as a multi-page PDF document to share a snapshot of your analytics without requiring access to Sellfaster.

### How to export

1. Open the dashboard you want to export
2. Click the **Export PDF** button in the dashboard toolbar
3. Sellfaster captures all visible widgets at 2Ã— resolution and composes them into an A4 PDF
4. The file downloads automatically to your browser's default download location

The export includes every widget currently visible on the dashboard. Widgets are rendered at high resolution using html2canvas and assembled into pages with jsPDF.

